snippet.textDisplay: I am blown away. Like truly blown away, thinking about how someone can stay as peaceful as the Nepali singer. Amidst all these 'musical' chaos, she is not even flexing a muscle, shaking her head, enjoying the beautiful music around her, she is just as peaceful as a stone, as peaceful as the core of this world itself. And Rahman sir, the lyricist, all the other musicians, this is magic. I think all of us at times lose hope about humanity itself, the kindness, goodness and all the love in this world sometimes feel so dead and buried. At such times, I listen to music like these, go through the comment section, because, I am sure all I will find there will be love, togetherness, kindness and positivity. And that brings back hope in my heart, that may be, just may be all is not dead until we have musicians like ARR. Thank you for this.
